The United States economy is experiencing a positive trend in job growth, with an average of 207,000 jobs created per month in 2018. This exceeds the average monthly gains in 2016 and 2017. Since President Trump took office, 3.6 million jobs have been created, with over 4 million new jobs since the election in November 2016. Various sectors, such as construction, manufacturing, transportation and warehousing, and mining and logging, have seen significant job growth. Additionally, average weekly earnings have increased by 3.2 percent over the past year, while nominal hourly earnings have increased by 2.9 percent. The unemployment rate is also at a historic low, with the U-6 unemployment rate falling to 7.4 percent, the lowest since April 2001. The rate of new unemployment claims is also at a record low. These indicators suggest a strong and booming economy in the United States.